1. What is the user used to execute the sleep process within the ubuntu-sleeper pod?
A:
$ kubectl exec ubuntu-sleeper -- whoami

//k exec is to to execute commands directly inside a running container within a Kubernetes pod
//The general structure of the command is:
//kubectl exec (POD_NAME) [-c CONTAINER_NAME] [FLAGS] -- COMMAND [ARGUMENTS]
// --: A mandatory separator used to distinguish kubectl flags from the command being run inside the container. 


